7 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
8 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 858.314 of Title 59, unless
9 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
10 A. A wholesaler shall:
11 1. Disclose in writing to the homeowner, before the execution
12 of any contract or written agreement, his or her intent to assign or
13 sell his or her equitable interest in the residential real estate
14 for a higher price than what is offered to the homeowner;
15 2. Provide a prominent written disclosure to the homeowner in
16 all written contracts between the parties stating that the homeowner
17 should seek legal advice before signing any contract concerning his
18 or her home; and
19 3. Disclose in writing to the homeowner that the homeowner has
20 the right to cancel the contract without penalty within seven (7)
21 business days after the execution of the contract.
22 B. A wholesaler shall not, directly or indirectly:
23
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1075 SFLR Page 7
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. Act as an advisor or consultant, or in any other manner
2 representing that the wholesaler is acting on behalf of the
3 homeowner; or
4 2. Represent himself or herself as holding a certification or
5 license, or being a member of a licensed profession, without
6 possession of the certification or license.
7 C. The homeowner shall have the right to cancel the contract
8 without penalty within seven (7) business days from the date of
9 execution of the contract.
10 D. The wholesaler shall be prohibited from placing any lien or
11 encumbrance on or otherwise clouding title of the property.
12 E. Any contract or agreement used by a wholesaler shall contain
13 the following:
14 1. The name, address, and telephone number of the wholesaler;
15 2. The address of the residence involved in the transaction;
16 3. The total consideration to be given by the wholesaler to the
17 homeowner;
18 4. A complete description of the terms of payment or other
19 consideration including, but not limited to, any services of any
20 nature which the wholesaler represents he or she will perform for
21 the seller before or after the sale; and
22 5. The following notice shall appear on the contract in
23 immediate proximity to the space reserved for the seller’s signature
24 and shall be in at least twelve-point bold type if the contract is
